Statements: c-jun negatively regulates the expression of pten by binding to the activator protein 1 site of the pten promoter , resulting in the concomitant activation of the akt pathway .

consistent with these in vivo findings , more recent in vitro studies have suggested a mechanism by which extensive tcr stimulation is detrimental for the generation of induced t reg cells ; constitutive or prolonged signaling through the akt – pi3k – mtor pathway , which is downstream of the tcr , antagonizes the induction of foxp3 ( haxhinasto et al ., 2008 ; sauer et al ., 2008 ) .
